article.headline: Wichita St. 61, Indiana St. 45
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Kyle Wilson scored 15 points and Wichita State held Indiana State to one basket over the game's final 14:09 to win 61-45 Thursday night. Wichita State (16-9, 7-7 Missouri Valley) has won three of its past four games. Wilson was 5-of-8 shooting, including 3-for-4 from 3-point range. P.J. Couisnard added 10 points for the Shockers. Wichita State led 26-24 at halftime. After Indiana State (12-12, 5-9) tied the game at 40-40 on Jay Tunnell's basket with 14:09 to play, the Shockers responded with a 12-0 run over the next 7:37 to go up 52-40. Gabe Moore made a 3-pointer with 6:32 remaining to make it 52-43, but that was Indiana State's last bucket of the game. The Sycamores' only other points came on Harry Marshall's two free throws with 1:55 to go. Moore, Marshall and Trent Wurtz scored 10 points apiece to lead Indiana State. Indiana State has lost eight of its past nine games since beating the Shockers 68-63 on Jan. 10 in Terre Haute, Ind.
